                {"src": "ellicott", "attr": "Ellicott's Commentary", "html": "<p>To <em>have no fellowship</em> with the works of darkness does not merely mean refusing to participate in them—that should go without saying. It means keeping no terms with them, having no sympathy, no indulgence, no excuse for them. The believer is not to be a neutral observer of evil but an active exposer of it—a light that shows darkness what it is by the sheer contrast of its own character.</p>"},
